`invoke` starts an actor bound to a state's lifetime — it stops when the state exits. `spawn` creates a long-lived actor stored in context; you can spawn many (e.g. one per file) and reference them via `ActorRefFrom`. Here each START event spawns a child download actor and stores its ref; spawned actors survive across state transitions.

